The first Principals Committee Meeting on Advancing Equity, convened by Domestic Policy Advisor Susan Rice, took place today. This meeting was in response to President Biden's Executive Order on advancing equity and support for underserved communities. The Committee, chaired by Rice, consists of Cabinet-level leaders from all federal agencies and senior White House officials. The purpose of the meeting was to discuss how to enact a comprehensive approach to advancing equity throughout federal policies and institutions. During the virtual meeting, Cabinet leaders and senior officials shared their progress in integrating equity and racial justice into the federal government's highest levels. They also affirmed their commitment to ensuring that the President's Executive Order results in significant work to advance equity. The meeting also addressed Office of Management and Budget (OMB) guidance to agencies on coordinating the implementation of the Order.